title: IN PHOTOS: Miss Universe candidates arrive in Manila
text:
IN PHOTOS: Miss Universe candidates arrive in Manila (UPDATED) The 65th Miss Universe candidates arrive in Manila ahead of the January 30 pageant Published 11:10 AM, January 12, 2017 Updated 12:56 PM, January 12, 2017 NOW IN MANILA. Miss Nicaragua Marina Jacoby greets those waiting for her at the airport after she lands in Manila. Photo courtesy of DOT 
MANILA, Philippines (UPDATED) – The candidates for the 65th Miss Universe pageant are here! 
Many of the Miss Universe candidates are landing in Manila on January 12 and 13, with Miss Costa Rica Carolina Duran and Miss Nicaragua Marina Jacoby arriving first. ([READ] Miss Universe 2016: Everything you need to know about the pageant ) Miss Costa Rica Carolina Duran. Photo courtesy of DOT 
Here's a look at all the 65th Miss Universe ladies at the airport. This page will be updated as more of the ladies arrive. 
Miss USA Deshauna Barber A photo posted by Deshauna Barber (@missusa) on Jan 11, 2017 at 8:02pm PST 
Miss Canada Siera Bearchell and Miss British Virgin Islands Erika Creque 
In the photo below, Deshauna, Siera, and Erika pose with Department of Tourism (DOT) Undersecretary Kat de Castro. DOT Undersecretary Katherine de Castro with Miss USA Deshauna Barber, Miss Canada Siera Bearchell, and Miss British Virgin Islands Erika Creque. Photo courtesy of DOT 
A few days before January 12, 6 candidates arrived ahead of the rest: Miss US Virgin Islands Carolyn Carter, Miss Guyana Soyini Fraser, Miss Brazil Raissa Santana, Miss Sierra Leone Hawa Kamara , Miss Thailand Chalita Suansane, and Miss Albania Lindita Idrizi. (IN PHOTOS: First Miss Universe candidates arrive in Manila ) A photo posted by CAROLYN CARTER (@carolyncarter) on Jan 7, 2017 at 7:08am PST A photo posted by 65thMissUniverse (@65thmissuniverse) on Jan 8, 2017 at 10:19pm PST A photo posted by Raissa Santana (@santana_raissa) on Jan 9, 2017 at 1:46am PST A photo posted by Chalita Suansane (@namtanlitaa) on Jan 10, 2017 at 4:20am PST 
Aside from the Miss Universe candidates, representatives from the organization are set to visit Manila for the pageant too. 
Of course, Miss Universe 2015 Pia Wurtzbach will be in the country as well, to crown her successor on coronation night, January 30. 
Before the big night and the preliminary competition, the ladies will tour the country , attend events like fashion shows and charities, and even meet President Rodrigo Duterte. – Rappler.com HOW DOES THIS STORY MAKE YOU FEEL? Happy
